Description. Male ( Holotype ). Cephalothorax and legs brownish yellow. Abdomen dorsally pale yellow with grayish transverse black stripes (
Fig. 20
), ventral surface and spinnerets pale yellow (Figs. 37–38 ). Total length, including chelicerae: 5.12 . Cephalothorax 1.92 long, 1.50 wide, with short, longitudinal fovea (
Fig. 20
). Chelicerae 1.05 long, porrect, with large anterior knobs (Fig. 33 ) distally with irregular row of 16–18 stiff black setae and two long spurs (
Figs. 6–7
). Basal segment of chelicerae with 11–12 promarginal irregular teeth in row and no teeth on retromargin (
Fig. 8
). Rastellum absent. Intercheliceral tumescence absent. Clypeus 0.10 wide. Eight eyes on black tubercle. Anterior eye row straight, posterior row slightly recurved. Eye diameter: AME 0.12 , ALE 0.23 , PLE 0.10 , PME 0.08 . Overall shape of eye group trapezoidal, wider than long.
